-----------------------------------------------------

> https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/pricing/tco/calculator/
> Uses to estimate the cost savings you can realize by migrating your workloads to Azure.

Azure Cost Management :
-----------------------

> Subscriptions > we can see current cost and forecost bill as per our usage > If we click on cost analysis > we can see actual cost and forecast cost for the month > scroll down > you can see accumulated cost as per the resource, location and resource group
> we can apply filters to see bill for the particular resource.

An Example Invoice :
--------------------

> open Cost Management and Billing > invoices > open sample invoices
> you can check cost per resource by scroll down
> If you want to see detailed information, click on "Prepare Azure usage file" located on the top of same page > download and open the csv file and analyse your bill.
> If you have any queries about your bill, you can contact support call with azure engineer and convey your explaination.

Creating budgets in Azure :
---------------------------

> We can set threshold budget for month. so that we can control our billing per month.
> subscription > Budgets > Add > name, period, budget amount, alert condition, create email address, create.
> By creating budgets we can get notified once our bill is reached to the threshold. So that we can clean up our unnecessary resources of azure.

Support options in Azure :
--------------------------

> If we encounters any issues, we can raise ticket at Help support.
> Basic : for all azure customers. (no 24/7 support)
> Developer : $29/month ( available during business hours only by email )
> Standard : $100/month
> Professional Direct : $1000/month ( Immediate support 24/7, with in hour they will respond )

Azure Service Level Agreements :
--------------------------------

> https://www.microsoft.com/licensing/docs/view/Service-Level-Agreements-SLA-for-Online-Services?lang=1
> Read the SLA's to learn about azure uptime guarantees and downtime credit policies.
> Monthly uptime % = ( Maximum Available Minutes-Downtime)/Maximum Available Minutes X 100

Monthly uptime %	Service Credit
================	==============
< 99.99%				10%
< 99%					25%
< 95%					100%

Business Metrics :
------------------

> https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/architecture/framework/resiliency/business-metrics
> Usful for companies

SLA	Downtime/week	downtime/month 	downtime/year
--- -------------	--------------	-------------
99%		1.68hours	7.2 hours		3.65 days
99.9%	10.1minuts	43.2 minutes	8.76 hours
99.95%	5minuts 	21.6minutes		4.38 hours
99.99%	1.01minuts	4.32 minutes	52.56 minutes
99.999%	6 seconds	25.9 seconds	5.26 minutes

