Resource tags :
---------------

> Basics: This is used to add metadata yo your resources.
> Application: Tags can be applied to resources, resource groups and subscriptions.
> Costing: Tags can offer another way when it comes to filtering on costs.
> Inheritance: If a tag is applied at a resource group level, it is not applied to the resources in the reource groups.

Management Groups :
-------------------

> When any company have multiple subscriptions, then company manages all subscriptions with the help of management groups.

> Company can have multiple management groups under Tenant Root Group.

> Role based access control is applicable for management groups

> Azure policies are also applicable for Azure policies.

Azure Blueprints :
------------------

> Used to orchestrate deployments of artifacts to Azure.

> By creating, assigning and publishing Bluprints, we can deploy artifacts from ARM templates, Azure poilicies, Resource groups, RBAC to new azure subscription.

Azure Policy :
--------------

> Using azure policies we can apply rules to our subscriptions.
> we can create our own policies.
> Default policies are also available.
> we can assign policies management group level, subscription levele or resource group level.

Azure resource locks :
----------------------

> It prvents accedental deletion / modification of our resource.
> Ex : Open storage accounts > Locks ( Read only / Delete ) > Add Lock > Ok---> Then we can not modify our storage account if it is Ready only lock or we can not delete if it is Delete lock.


Azure CLI :
===========

> It is command line utility to manage azure resources.
> For this we need to install az cli tool in our machine ( Win/Linux/Mac ).
> By running az cli commands we can manage azure resources easily.
> Ex : to login to your account
	az login --> it will prompr azure login page in the browser, we should pass our credentials. so that we are able to login to our azure portal via cli
	
	az group list --> it will show list of resource groups in json format

Azure PowerShell and CloudShell :
=================================

> It is powerful tool to manage azure resources and other resources.
> we need to install Azure  Az PowerShell module from The PowerShell Gallery. or we can use it from your azure portal.
> shell.azure.com
> When we open cloudshell for the first time, it creates storage account to store your files at particular region.
> Once cloudshell is opened, you can switch to powershell or shell mode.
> using cloudshell we can easily manages azure resources and also third party resources.

ARM templates :
===============

> We can define infrastructure as code.
> Create an Azure Resource Manager template.
> This is a JavaScript Object Notation (JSON) file that actually contains the defination of the infrastructure.
> You can store the ARM templates in your source code repository along with your application code.
> Microsoft has also release a new language called Bicep that has the same capabilities as ARM templates.
> Bicep just uses a syntax that is easier to use.
> We can use Template deployment service / powershell / cloudshell / azure cli to deploy the ARM templates.

Note on the Azure Arc resources :
---------------------------------

> This is centralized service, by using this service we can manage azure resources and on-premesis environment.

Azure Advisor :
---------------

> This service gives us recommendations based on countries on Cost, Security, Reliability, Operational Excellence, Performance etc.


Azure Service Health :
----------------------

> Open Help + support > click on Service Health
> We can browse Service issues, Planned maintenence, Health advaisories, Health history [ > we can create service health alert ], Security advaisories, Resource Health etc.

Azure Monitor service :
-----------------------

> We can monitor azure services and creates monitor alerts based on alert rules.
> we can check metrics for the resources.
> Ex: for vm, based on cpu utilization is goes beyond the threshold, it triggers the alert.

Log Analytics :
---------------

> Using this service, we can collect data from any azure resource ( vm ) by using data collection rules in the log analytics workspace.
> This service is centralized system to storing the logs.

Application Insights :
----------------------

> Application Insights in an extension of Azure Monitor and provides application performance monitoring ( APM ) features. APM tools are useful to monitor applications from development, through test, and into production in the following ways :
	1. Proactives understand how an application is performing.
	2. Reactively review application execution data to determine the cause of an incident.

